# .hypatia-ignore — repo-scoped exemptions for the Hypatia neurosymbolic
# scanner (Hypatia.ScannerSuppression).
#
# Format (one per line; '#' = comment; blank lines tolerated):
#   <rule_module>/<rule_type>:<path-fragment>   # one rule, paths CONTAINING fragment
#   <rule_module>/*:<path-fragment>             # any type in that module
#   <path-fragment>                             # any rule, any module
# Matching is a SUBSTRING test against the repo-relative path.
#
# Every entry below is a VERIFIED false positive on pre-existing RSR-template
# scaffolding — confirmed 2026-06-21 by reproducing the scan and reading each
# flagged line. None mask a real vulnerability; the genuinely dangerous shapes
# of each rule (untrusted input in a run: step, a live unpinned action, a real
# committed secret, plaintext HTTP to a public host) are absent.

# ── code_safety: proof-stub prohibition comments matched as the banned token ──
# The Idris2/Coq proof STUBS under verification/proofs/ carry header comments
# that FORBID the escape hatches, e.g.:
#   "-- All proofs MUST be constructive (no believe_me, no assert_total)."
#   "All proofs must be complete — NO Admitted allowed."
# The scanner matches the token inside the comment that prohibits it.
code_safety/believe_me:verification/proofs
code_safety/assert_total:verification/proofs
code_safety/admitted:verification/proofs

# ── code_safety: internal container service-discovery URLs ──
# http:// targets in the container compose files are private service names on
# the pod/compose network (http://panoply:8080, http://rust-api:8080,
# http://elixir-worker:4000), not public endpoints. HTTPS does not apply.
code_safety/http_url:container/

# ── workflow_audit: safe GitHub Actions expression usage ──
# Every ${{ }} flagged in these template workflows is a trusted context value
# (github.repository, *.sha, github.ref_name) or is assigned to an env: var
# (the recommended indirection) — never untrusted input interpolated into a
# run: shell. The rule flags syntactic presence regardless of the mitigation.
workflow_audit/actions_expression_injection:.github/workflows/

# ── workflow_audit: commented-out example `uses:` lines ──
# release.yml carries documentation examples like
#   "# - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4"
# which are comments, not live (unpinned) steps.
workflow_audit/unpinned_action:.github/workflows/release.yml

# ── workflow_audit: setup-script bootstrap fetch ──
# build/setup.sh's bootstrap download-then-run is the script's documented
# purpose, not drift.
workflow_audit/download_then_run:build/setup.sh
